Title:
EDRUnChoker — Fileless WMI remediation for EDRChoker QoS throttling

Type:
GitHub Tool

Short Summary (4–8 sentences max):
EDRUnChoker is a defensive PowerShell toolkit that mitigates EDRChoker’s abuse of Windows QoS (via `pacer.sys`) to throttle EDR/AV agent network telemetry to near-zero bandwidth. It deploys a fileless, permanent WMI event subscription in `root\subscription` that runs on a 5-second timer and executes embedded VBScript to enumerate and remove malicious QoS policies. The key implementation detail is enumerating QoS policies using WMI with `WbemContext` `PolicyStore` against both `ActiveStore` and `GPO:localhost`, because plain WMI `ExecQuery` can miss ActiveStore policies created by `New-NetQosPolicy`/EDRChoker. It targets throttles applied to known security product executables or policies with aggressive low rates (≤1 Mbps). The tool also logs remediation actions to the Windows Application log under provider `EDRChokerDefense` for SOC visibility and correlation. It’s primarily useful for Blue Teams/IR and endpoint engineering teams responding to or hardening against telemetry-suppression attacks.

Technical Focus:
- Windows QoS policy abuse and remediation (`New-NetQosPolicy`, `pacer.sys`)
- Permanent WMI event subscriptions (`root\subscription`, timers, consumers)
- WMI policy enumeration via `WbemContext` `PolicyStore` (ActiveStore vs GPO)
- Fileless persistence/automation using VBScript embedded in WMI consumers
- Windows Event Log instrumentation for remediation evidence
- Sysmon monitoring of WMI subscription tampering (Event IDs 19/20/21)

Use Cases:
- Detect and automatically remove malicious QoS throttling policies targeting EDR agents
- Host-based remediation during incident response to restore endpoint telemetry
- Continuous hardening/guardrail to prevent re-application of EDRChoker-style policies
- SOC correlation via Application log events and forwarding through WEF/Splunk/Elastic
- Baseline and alert on WMI subscription changes indicating defense tampering

Keywords:
EDRUnChoker, EDRChoker, QoS throttling, pacer.sys, New-NetQosPolicy, Get-NetQosPolicy, WMI, root\\subscription, permanent event subscription, __EventFilter, ActiveScriptEventConsumer, WbemContext, PolicyStore, ActiveStore, GPO:localhost, VBScript, PowerShell, Sysmon 19, Sysmon 20, Sysmon 21, Windows Application log, telemetry suppression